  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47a621783cb453147b01764dde5ed130, type: 3}
  m_Name: R2_4_WriteEnergyRecipe
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - This brew also requires repeated stirring.
  - Certain ingredients need time to blend properly with the magic around them.
  - Instead of writing the same stirring step several times, Moonwardens condensed
    repetead actions into patterns.
  - You're now ready to write the recipe for the Emberroot Brew.
  - Remember the sequence carefully.
  - First, light the fire under the cauldron.
  - Then add two potatoes, followed by a Carrot.
  - Finally, stir the brew exactly three times.
  - Excellent. You noticed the repeated action, didn't you?
  - Patterns exist everywhere in magic, dear.
  - The more you learn to notice them, the more naturally potioncraft will come to
    you.
  - It keeps recipes easier to read... and easier to understand.
